            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Quick Tips -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">üí°</span>
          Quick Tips
        </div>
        <div class="tips-grid">
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">üö´</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>Never try new foods</strong> on race day. Test everything in training first.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">üíß</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>Hydration starts</strong> the day before. Drink consistently, not just during runs.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">‚è∞</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>The 30-min window</strong> post-workout is critical. Your muscles are primed to absorb nutrients.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">üçå</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>Simple carbs during</strong>, complex carbs before. Match fuel to timing.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">üèÉ</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>For 120+ min runs:</strong> practice fueling during training‚Äîyour gut needs training too.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tip-item">
            <span class="tip-icon">‚ö°</span>
            <span class="tip-text"><strong>Hitting the wall?</strong> You waited too long to fuel. Start eating at 45-60 min mark.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="page-footer">
      <span>Fuel Like a Runner</span> ‚Ä¢ Keep this page handy for quick reference during training
    </div>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
